Difficulties are already starting to appear. I'm probably going to have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it's going to take ENORMOUS amounts of time and require A LOT more work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and for now, it seems *completely* surmountable. It's just that it's going to take a lot of time and $$.
In case the challenge that awaits me interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. They don't issue a medical certificate if you're undergoing treatment for it.
